The paper deals with complexity measures and lower bounds in communication complexity, which are central topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of critical block sensitivity as a complexity measure suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses monotone circuit depth and proof complexity, which are topics related to logic and complexity theory (cs.LO). The study of communication complexity often involves information theory and coding theory, which are covered in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG) due to the use of Tseitin and Pebbling search problems, which are related to graph theory and geometric algorithms.
